Description: Reliable USB Formatting Utility
 Rufus is a utility that helps format and create bootable USB flash
 drives, such as USB keys/pendrives, memory sticks, etc.
 .
 It is useful for cases where you need to create USB installation media
 from bootable ISOs (Windows, Linux, UEFI, etc.), or where you need to
 work with a device that has no OS installed, or where you need to flash
 a BIOS or other firmware from DOS.
 .
 Rufus supports a wide range of bootable image formats (ISO/IMG/VHD/VHDX),
 filesystem types (FAT16/FAT32/NTFS/exFAT/ext2/ext3/ext4/UDF), and
 partition schemes (MBR/GPT) for both BIOS and UEFI targets.
 .
 On Linux, Rufus uses GTK3 for its graphical interface and can also operate
 in headless/CLI mode via command-line arguments.
